Step 1: Identify the necessary components.  
• From the income statement, the Main Business Revenue for the period is 5,991,764.34.  
• From the balance sheet, the Total Assets at the beginning of the period are 13,000,000.00 and Total Assets at the end of the period are 15,288,131.32.

Step 2: Compute the Average Total Assets.  
Average Total Assets = (Beginning Total Assets + Ending Total Assets) / 2  
  = (13,000,000.00 + 15,288,131.32) / 2  
  = 28,288,131.32 / 2  
  = 14,144,065.66

Step 3: Calculate the Total Asset Turnover Ratio.  
Total Asset Turnover Ratio = Total Revenue / Average Total Assets  
  = 5,991,764.34 / 14,144,065.66  
  ≈ 0.4237

Step 4: Rounding the result (to two decimal places) gives approximately 0.42.

Thus, the solution is:
